To integrate Stripe payment gateway in a Django application, you should follow these steps:

1. Install the required packages:

You'll need to install the Stripe package to enable communication between your Django application and Stripe's API. You can do this using pip:

```
python -m pip install stripe
```

2. Configure your Stripe keys:

Inside your Django settings.py file, add your Stripe secret key and publishable key. You can get these keys from the API keys section in your Stripe account.

```python
# settings.py

STRIPE_PUBLIC_KEY = 'your-stripe-publishable-key'
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY = 'your-stripe-secret-key'
```

3. Create views for the payment process:

We will create views to render the payment page and handle the payment process.

```python
# views.py

from django.shortcuts import render, redirect
import stripe
from django.conf import settings

stripe.api_key = settings.STRIPE_SECRET_KEY

def payment(request):
    # Render the payment page with the Stripe publishable key
    context = {
        'stripe_publishable_key': settings.STRIPE_PUBLIC_KEY
    }
    return render(request, 'payment.html', context)

def charge(request):
    if request.method == 'POST':
        amount = 100  # Amount in cents
        token = request.POST.get('stripeToken')

        try:
            # Create the charge
            charge = stripe.Charge.create(
                amount=amount,
                currency='usd',
                description='Example charge',
                source=token,
            )
            return redirect('success')
        except stripe.error.CardError as e:
            # Handle the payment card error
            return redirect('error')

def payment_success(request):
    return render(request, 'success.html')

def payment_error(request):
    return render(request, 'error.html')
```

4. Create corresponding templates for the payment page and success/error pages:

Create the following templates inside your Django templates folder:

- payment.html
- success.html
- error.html

Here's an example of payment.html that creates a payment form using Stripe.js:

```html
<!-- payment.html -->

{% load static %}

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>Stripe Payment</title>
  <script src="https://js.stripe.com/v3/"></script>
</head>
<body>

  <form method="post" action="{% url 'charge' %}" id="payment-form">
    {% csrf_token %}
    <div id="card-element">
      <!-- Elements to gather card details will show here -->
    </div>

    <button id="submit">Submit Payment</button>
  </form>

  <!-- Initialize Stripe.js -->
  <script>
  var stripe = Stripe('{{ stripe_publishable_key }}');

  var elements = stripe.elements();
  var cardElement = elements.create('card');
  cardElement.mount('#card-element');

  var form = document.getElementById('payment-form');
  form.addEventListener('submit', function(event) {
    event.preventDefault();

    stripe.createToken(cardElement).then(function(result) {
      if (result.error) {
        console.log(result.error.message);
      } else {
        var tokenInput = document.createElement('input');
        tokenInput.type = 'hidden';
        tokenInput.name = 'stripeToken';
        tokenInput.value = result.token.id;
        form.appendChild(tokenInput);

        form.submit();
      }
    });
  });
  </script>

</body>
</html>
```

5. Update your Django application's URL configuration:

Modify your Django application's urls.py to include the views you created.

```python
# urls.py

from django.urls import path
from . import views

urlpatterns = [
    path('payment/', views.payment, name='payment'),
    path('charge/', views.charge, name='charge'),
    path('success/', views.payment_success, name='success'),
    path('error/', views.payment_error, name='error'),
]
```

After completing these steps, you will have successfully integrated the Stripe payment gateway into your Django application.

