Here's a simple PHP function to paginate an array:

```php
function paginateArray($inputArray, $itemsPerPage, $currentPage) {
    $totalItems = count($inputArray);

    // Calculate total pages
    $totalPages = ceil($totalItems / $itemsPerPage);

    // Ensure the current page is within a valid range
    if ($currentPage < 1) {
        $currentPage = 1;
    } elseif ($currentPage > $totalPages) {
        $currentPage = $totalPages;
    }

    // Calculate the starting index for the current page
    $startIndex = ($currentPage - 1) * $itemsPerPage;

    // Slice the input array to get the desired portion for the current page
    $pagedArray = array_slice($inputArray, $startIndex, $itemsPerPage);

    // Return the paginated array and the total pages
    return [
        "pagedArray" => $pagedArray,
        "totalPages" => $totalPages,
    ];
}
```

